kerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22041837/propain-yuma-bad-mint-kids-full-suspension-mtb-140mm-travel-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22041837/propain-yuma-bad-mint-kids-full-suspension-mtb-140mm-travel-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22041837/propain-yuma-bad-mint-kids-full-suspension-mtb-140mm-travel-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22041837/propain-yuma-bad-mint-kids-full-suspension-mtb-140mm-travel-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 630w\"></a></p><p>Propain have retained the “grows with your child” concept, the standout feature that makes this bike popular among children and their parents alike. How does it work? The single-pivot full suspension Yuma is effectively two bikes in one; a flip-chip and Grown-Up Kit converts it from the Rookie Launcher 24″ bike to bike that can accommodate 26″ wheels.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031753/propain-yuma-kids-bike-flip-chip-wheel-size-change-dropouts.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031753/propain-yuma-kids-bike-flip-chip-wheel-size-change-dropouts.jpg\" alt=\"propain yuma flip chip adjusts chainstay length switch 24&quot; wheels to 26&quot;\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031753/propain-yuma-kids-bike-flip-chip-wheel-size-change-dropouts.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031753/propain-yuma-kids-bike-flip-chip-wheel-size-change-dropouts-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/