lip-chip-wheel-size-change-dropouts-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031753/propain-yuma-kids-bike-flip-chip-wheel-size-change-dropouts-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031753/propain-yuma-kids-bike-flip-chip-wheel-size-change-dropouts-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031753/propain-yuma-kids-bike-flip-chip-wheel-size-change-dropouts-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031753/propain-yuma-kids-bike-flip-chip-wheel-size-change-dropouts-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The flip-chip increases the chainstay length from 420mm to 432mm, increasing the wheelbase. When your kid has outgrown the 24″ wheels, both in terms of height and ability, you won’t need to buy an entirely new bike; just upgrade the one they have. This could be a seriously economical purchase, especially for families with two children with just the right age gap.</p><figure id=\"attachment_262446\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-262446\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031823/propain-yuma-kids-mtb-shock-frame-bag.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031823/propain-yuma-kids-mtb-shock-frame-bag.jpg\" alt=\"propain yuma kids mtb frame bag\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031823/propain-yuma-kids-mtb-shock-frame-bag.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/22031823/propain-yuma-kids-mtb-shock-frame-bag-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumo